# Media Capture — auction-scraper

## Screenshots Captured

| File | Sequence | Content |
|---|---|---|
| `01-initial.png` | Initial state | Demo page load: navbar, h1 "🏺 Auction Scraper", three action buttons ("Run Scraper", "Export JSON", "View Dataset") |
| `02-running.png` | Scrape started | Button clicked, UI showing loading state |
| `03-mid-stream.png` | Lots flowing in (~2s into SSE stream) | First 6–8 lots visible, columns layout, lot cards with images + metadata (lot #, estimate, date, sale location) |
| `04-final.png` | All results loaded | Full 18-lot grid (5 from bonhams, 8 from heritage_auctions, 5 from leland_little); each card shows lot image, lot number, description, estimate range, auction date, sale location, source label |
| `05-export-json.png` | Export feature | JSON export dialog showing raw structured data payload with consistent field schema across all sources |

## Video Captured

**File:** `page@71b4a9a8415cbd1c635d179bf35c71e1.webm` (660 KB, WebM format)

**Duration:** ~25 seconds (full hero flow from page load → "Run Scraper" click → SSE stream to completion)

**Content:** Deterministic end-to-end hero flow:
- Page load (0–3s): navbar, header, buttons visible, 0 console errors
- Button click & SSE stream (3–22s): lot cards render incrementally as server sends events; visual confirmation of streaming architecture
- Completion (22–25s): final count, Export JSON feature demonstrated

